"Message status history shows direct and indirect actions or errors related to the issue:
• The sequence of events that led to the current issue • The timeline of events and the time between events • History of events, such as a message that can’t be sent or delivered • What happened to the sent or received message before and after the issue • Any change between the message content received and the message content viewed by the receiver • Interruptions to Wi-Fi, data, and other types of connectivity • How a message with an issue affected other messages or the entire conversation"

"You can select which messages and conversations, if any, to include in your feedback. Only info about your messages and conversations is sent to Google, not the text or attachments in those messages.
Info about your messages and conversations includes phone numbers and email of senders and receivers, message type (SMS, MMS, or RCS), message size and any subject line, sent and received dates, local message and conversation IDs, local message status, and the internal message path (URL). Your text and attachments are not sent to Google.
This info helps validate assumptions and identify factors contributing to the issue, for faster, more efficient understanding of the issue."
